    <pre><code># E-commerce Order Analytics Pipeline

**Industry:** E-commerce | **Level:** Foundation → Intermediate
**Stack:** Python 3.11 · PySpark 3.5 · AWS S3 · AWS Glue · Athena · Parquet

## Business Problem
A mid-size e-commerce company had order data across 3 source systems.
BI analysts waited 3–4 days for manual data pulls. This pipeline automates
ingestion, transformation, and serving — reducing wait time to under 1 hour.

## Architecture
```
[MySQL CSV] [Returns JSON] [Events JSON]
      ↓            ↓             ↓
    S3 Raw Zone (partitioned by date)
            ↓
    AWS Glue PySpark ETL
    (validate → transform → load)
            ↓
    S3 Processed Zone (Parquet, Snappy)
            ↓
    AWS Athena (serverless SQL)
```

## Key Technical Decisions
- **Star schema** for analytical query performance (4 dims + 1 fact)
- **Parquet + Snappy** compression — 60-70% smaller than CSV
- **Partitioned by year/month** — Athena scans only relevant data
- **MD5 surrogate keys** — decouples warehouse from source system IDs
- **Data quality framework** — quarantines bad rows before they reach analysts

## How to Run Locally
```bash
pip install pyspark pandas boto3 faker
python3 scripts/generate_data.py    # create test data
python3 scripts/glue_etl_job.py     # run ETL
python3 scripts/data_quality.py     # validate output
```

## Business Impact
- Analyst wait time: 3–4 days → under 1 hour
- ETL processes 5,000 orders in ~45 seconds
- Athena query cost reduced ~70% via partitioning
- Data quality checks catch 98%+ of upstream issues</code></pre>
